definitions.definition: A port city and comune , the capital of the Metropolitan City of Venice and the region of Veneto , Italy ; former capital of an independent republic.
A metropolitan city of Veneto , established in 2015; in full, the Metropolitan City of Venice .
A former polity in Europe , a republic and colonial empire around the Adriatic and eastern Mediterranean from CE 697 to 1797 with its capital at Venice.
A township in Illinois , United States .
A township in Michigan , United States .
A township in Ohio , United States .
A neighborhood of Los Angeles , California , United States .
